Skip ghc-pkg recache during cross-compilation.

When cross-compiling, the ghc-pkg binary in the bindist is for the target
architecture and cannot execute on the build machine. The package.cache
will be regenerated by the bindist's configure/install process on the
target machine.

--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/BinaryDist.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/BinaryDist.hs
@@ -194,12 +194,17 @@ bindistRules = do
         copyDirectory (rtsIncludeDir)         bindistFilesDir
         when windowsHost $ createGhcii (bindistFilesDir -/- "bin")

-        -- Call ghc-pkg recache, after copying so the package.cache is
-        -- accurate, then it's on the distributor to use `cp -a` to install
-        -- a relocatable bindist.
-        --
-        -- N.B. the ghc-pkg executable may be prefixed with a target triple
-        -- (c.f. #20267).
-        ghcPkgName <- programName (vanillaContext Stage1 ghcPkg)
-        cmd_ (bindistFilesDir -/- "bin" -/- ghcPkgName) ["recache"]
+        -- Call ghc-pkg recache to make package.cache accurate
+        -- Skip this during cross-compilation since the ghc-pkg binary
+        -- in the bindist is for the target architecture and cannot run
+        -- on the build machine. The package.cache will be regenerated
+        -- by the bindist's configure/install process.
+        cross <- flag CrossCompiling
+        unless cross $ do
+            -- N.B. the ghc-pkg executable may be prefixed with a target triple
+            -- (c.f. #20267).
+            ghcPkgName <- programName (vanillaContext Stage1 ghcPkg)
+            cmd_ (bindistFilesDir -/- "bin" -/- ghcPkgName) ["recache"]


         -- The settings file must be regenerated by the bindist installation
